parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become stiff or difficult to turn, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.

loud banging or grinding noises when turning
vehicle wanders out of its lane.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion and failure of the steering column can cause loss of control and increase the risk of accidents, especially at slow speeds.
symptoms: steering wheel becomes stiff or difficult to turn
vehicle wanders out of its lane.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Deceptive Sales Practices and Failure to Disclose
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Deceptive sales practices and failure to disclose known issues can lead to buyers purchasing vehicles with hidden defects, which can cause safety risks and financial losses.
symptoms: Dealership fails to disclose known issues
fails to provide title or paperwork

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadequate recall repairs and service can lead to continued safety risks and failures, even after supposed repairs.
symptoms: manufacturers refuse to assist with repair costs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle can accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The engine revs to high RPM
the vehicle speeds up without pressing the gas pedal
the brakes may not fully stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inaccurate fuel gauge can lead to running out of fuel, causing inconvenience, and potentially stranding the driver.
symptoms: The fuel gauge does not register properly
the gauge jumps to a higher level when the fuel is low
the "Service Engine Soon" light is on constantly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank and Evaporative System Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Leaks in the fuel tank and evaporative system can cause fuel vapors to escape, leading to a fire hazard, and potentially causing accidents.

the vehicle fails inspection due to fuel tank leaks.
